{{Han compound|木|目|ls=ic|t1=tree|t2=eye}} – an eye looking at a tree — original character for {{och-l|相|to observe|id=2}}. Later {{Han phonetically borrowed}} to represent {{och-l|相|mutually|id=1}}.

===Etymology===
An [[allofam]] is {{och-l|胥|each other; mutually; all; to observe; to assist}} ({{zh-ref|Gong, 1995}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Note also similarities to {{cog|my|သင့်|t=to befall, be suitable}}.

Derivative: {{och-l|想|to think}} (“appearance > to visualise > to think”).

